nk:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533995\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xzp1665702623223.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xzp1665702623223.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xzp1665702623223.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xzp1665702623223\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Enable Referential Integrity in a Microsoft SQL Server Database\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">SQL scripts for referential integrity can be generated with the IDE command line switch <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/genSql</span>. The generated scripts map relationships defined in the application model to declarative constraints and database triggers in the database.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__context_w3439ab1b5b1_w3440ab1b5_w3441ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__topic_d53099e1_d53100e1_d53101e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__p_d53102e1_d53103e1_d53104e1\">To enable referential integrity in the database:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24887e1_d24888e1_d24889e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Set the connector option <code class=\"ph codeph\">DBMS ri</code> in the assignment file.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24890e1_d24891e1_d24892e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__p_d53105e1_d53106e1_d53107e1\">Add the following to the <span class=\"ph filepath\">mss_<var class=\"keyword varname\">entity.model</var>_createReferentialIntegrity.sql</span> scripts:\n where <var class=\"keyword varname\">DatabaseName</var>is the name of the database where the entities exist.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">use <var class=\"keyword varname\">DatabaseName</var>\ngo</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24893e1_d24894e1_d24895e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the SQL scripts to create referential integrity.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24896e1_d24897e1_d24898e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Load the data into the tables.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24899e1_d24900e1_d24901e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__p_d53108e1_d53109e1_d53110e1\">Add the following to the <span class=\"ph filepath\">mss_<var class=\"keyword varname\">entity.model</var>_validateReferentialIntegrity.sql</span> scripts:\n where <var class=\"keyword varname\">DatabaseName</var>is the name of the database where the entities exist.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">use <var class=\"keyword varname\">DatabaseName</var>\ngo</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24902e1_d24903e1_d24904e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Execute the SQL scripts to verify the referential integrity.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__result_w3442ab1b5b5_w3443ab1b5_w3444ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__p_d53111e1_d53112e1_d53113e1\">If you need to drop the referential integrity constraints for some reason:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24905e1_d24906e1_d24907e1\">Add the following to <span class=\"ph filepath\">mss_<var class=\"keyword varname\">entity.model</var>_deleteReferentialIntegrity.sql</span> scripts:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">use <var class=\"keyword varname\">DatabaseName</var>\ngo</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__p_d53114e1_d53115e1_d53116e1\">where <var class=\"keyword varname\">DatabaseName</var>is the name of the database where the entities exist.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xzp1665702623223__li_d24908e1_d24909e1_d24910e1\">Execute the SQL scripts to drop referential integrity constraints.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gei1665702926904.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Scripts</a><p>For most supported databases, you can generate SQL scripts to create the tables required for a Uniface Repository using the /genSql /createtable command line switch, also known as the Create Table facility.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533995\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533995\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Enable Referential Integrity in a Microsoft SQL Server Database Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Enable Referential Integrity in a Microsoft SQL Server Database SQL scripts for referential integrity can be generated with the IDE command line switch /genSql . The generated scripts map relationships defined in the application model to declarative constraints and database triggers in the database. To enable referential integrity in the database: Set the connector option DBMS ri in the assignment file. Add the following to the mss_ entity.model _createReferentialIntegrity.sql scripts: where DatabaseName is the name of the database where the entities exist. use DatabaseName go Copy Execute the SQL scripts to create referential integrity. Load the data into the tables. Add the following to the mss_ entity.model _validateReferentialIntegrity.sql scripts: where DatabaseName is the name of the database where the entities exist. use DatabaseName go Copy Execute the SQL scripts to verify the referential integrity. If you need to drop the referential integrity constraints for some reason: Add the following to mss_ entity.model _deleteReferentialIntegrity.sql scripts: use DatabaseName go Copy where DatabaseName is the name of the database where the entities exist. Execute the SQL scripts to drop referential integrity constraints. Related Links Database Scripts For most supported databases, you can generate SQL scripts to create the tables required for a Uniface Repository using the /genSql /createtable command line switch, also known as the Create Table facility. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}